</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="31F024AB4208AADA64B9EB4B0D4891DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="57ACE5F121370BBA3A7233EA20DC439C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="6918E1458DB7F04777032D75DFA06D45" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Mollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mollugo oppositifolia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oppositifolia">Mollugo oppositifolia</taxonomicName>
≡ 
<taxonomicName id="70449A067B452ACA872EBDD6B6191287" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Mollugo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mollugo oppositifolia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oppositifolia">Mollugo oppositifolia</taxonomicName>
L., Sp. Pl. 1: 89 (1753). 
<emphasis id="DB6A9BBB80CF745B6D839FC862BA33D8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Holotype</emphasis>
: Sri Lanka. 
<emphasis id="73F0960A7EBC275775A1727CA9EEC9D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. Hermann</emphasis>
in Herb. Hermann 1: fol. 20 (BM000621295!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D7EF452004C4DDD5A93470308A4A4FAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="F51CCC1292222794571CB52D3F6AF13D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A3C975E2E8905FED120E564517D8E67C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Annual, branched from the base, with numerous prostrate stems often forming mats up to 1 m in diameter; young parts of the stems covered with simple crispate hairs usually arranged along one line; prickles absent or unnoticeable with the naked eye. Leaves rosulate, short-lived, and cauline, green, glabrous or puberulent, shortly petiolate (petioles 3-10 mm long), entire or coarsely denticulate, oblong, ovate, obovate or narrowly obovate, (10)15-45(55) mm 
<normalizedToken id="F9F015431E3976D25EDE6299CD8978AB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-15(20) mm, apically shortly acuminate, lateral veins neither recessed adaxially nor prominent abaxially. Flower clusters interrupted, consisting of (1)2-10 flowers, rarely more; flowers usually with unequal pedicels 7.0-20.0 mm long, or sometimes (sub)sessile; buds and closed anthocarp of cylindrical shape. Perianth segments in flowering (2.7)3.0-3.5 mm long, in fruiting (3.5)4.0-5.0(5.5) mm long, glabrous or sparsely pubescent, dorsally green or pink with white margins and ventrally white or pinkish, sometimes turning red at senescence; petaloids usually absent. Stamens usually 5, rarely 4 or 6-7; anthers (03.-0.5)0.6-0.8(1.0) mm long. Stigmas 3, 0.3-0.6 mm long. Seeds reddish or brown-red, rarely yellow-brown, 0.30-0.50 
<normalizedToken id="FF70A3DAA64D54CACCB32A6DC4CB45B0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(0.25)0.3-0.4 mm, colliculate or rarely smooth, longitudinal ridges absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B24E24058556E05AF92853B5788C9509" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="FEB709292D0342BAF701BBACE94DCE52" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E7CAC216E22307FCAB8A375AB15178A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="A61EC64F83601CA1B5F22DF0D1483008" authorityName="Aug. DC., Bull. Herb. Boiss., ser. 2, 1: 559" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="L." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Corbichoniaceae" genus="Glinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Glinus oppositifolius" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oppositifolius">
<emphasis id="F56C16EE62BCFE27E3ADCA5EB0B68EE9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Glinus oppositifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sometimes confused with 
<taxonomicName id="DCDE302A09E532AD883847E95165EAFF" class="Eudicots" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Gisekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gisekia pharnaceoides" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="pharnaceoides">
<emphasis id="8B358B9826D4C3B2C654CEE6571174CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gisekia pharnaceoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="A14111192CC1603C00B52468A935130B" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gisekiaceae" genus="Gisekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="family">Gisekiaceae</taxonomicName>
). The most remarkable characters of 
<taxonomicName id="288F001DA23EDBA67FB752BD585A4632" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" class="Eudicots" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Gisekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gisekia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98EFB6D68D5D3560FFAB41DB01E9A5EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gisekia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the leaves and perianth with white striae (formed by cells with raphides), and its capsules are divided into 5-15 mericarps each containing one exarillate seed (
<bibRefCitation id="677B46811C3EB2E6A4B69EA5FE2B9E38" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4117942" author="Gilbert, MG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="343 - 356" refId="B58" refString="Gilbert, MG, 1993b. A review of Gisekia (Gisekiaceae). Kew Bulletin 48 (2): 343 - 356, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4117942" title="A review of Gisekia (Gisekiaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4117942" volume="48" year="1993 b">Gilbert 1993b</bibRefCitation>
). In contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="91FF10A55C7CD3A34118D8CB218D4DBC" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1771" class="Eudicots" family="Molluginaceae" genus="Gisekia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gisekia" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="184924F5BD8B275AE648C45E8C21CF7B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gisekia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="61C6A8A38A2A351D26C6F5ADA11FB4E3" authorityName="L., Sp. Pl. 1: 463" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Corbichoniaceae" genus="Glinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Glinus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FE76B921035ADD8C86A4879712177E87" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Glinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species do not have easily visible raphides in any part of the plant and their capsules are multi-seeded with arillate seeds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
